Privacy Policy for ReadAid
Effective Date: December 1,2024.

At ReadAid, we are committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you use our mobile application. Please read this policy carefully to understand how we handle your data.

1. Information We Collect
a) Personal Information
We may collect the following personal information if required for app functionality:

Email address (e.g., for authentication via Google OAuth).
Account-related information necessary for login.
b) Non-Personal Information
We may collect non-identifiable data, such as:

Usage statistics (e.g., how users interact with app features).
Diagnostic data for troubleshooting and improving the app.
2. How We Use Your Information
We use the collected information for the following purposes:

To provide, maintain, and improve the functionality of ReadAid.
To analyze usage patterns and improve the app experience.
To ensure the security and proper functioning of the app.
3. Data Sharing
We do not sell or share your personal data with third parties except in the following situations:

Compliance with Law: When required by law or government requests.
Service Providers: We may use trusted third-party tools to enhance app functionality, but they are bound by confidentiality obligations.
4. Data Security
We take the security of your data seriously. We use reasonable administrative, technical, and physical safeguards to protect your information. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

5. Children's Privacy
ReadAid is designed for children but is intended to be used under parental supervision. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13 without parental consent. If you believe your child has provided personal information without your consent, please contact us to delete it.

6. Your Rights
You have the following rights regarding your data:

Access and Correction: You can request access to or correction of your personal data.
Data Deletion: You may request that we delete your personal information, subject to legal requirements.
To exercise these rights, contact us at the email below.

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted here with an updated "Effective Date." Continued use of ReadAid after changes signify your acceptance of the updated policy.

8. Contact Us
